        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-18 11:26:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI tend to think this should be initiated by MDD (unfortunately) because striping defaults are taken from the parent directory.\nplease have a look at mdd_create_data() which is called with we try to open objectless file for write.\n\nalso.. I just realized we may already have objectless files with size>0, so probably we can't remove old functionality right away (which I'd prefer to do). probably it makes sense to talk to Andreas about this compatibility issue.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "97ef99ce0254c8cb42b18f694e56e3c38eef8717",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-18 17:49:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I tend to think this should be initiated by MDD (unfortunately) because striping defaults are taken from the parent directory. please have a look at mdd_create_data() which is called with we try to open objectless file for write.\n\nBut in setattr() we do not have the parent at hand so mdd_create_data() will fall back to the LOD device defaults.  If this is the only reason for initiating from MDD then it would seem that nothing is gained.  Unless you want to find parent(s) in mdd_create_data().  Seems much cleaner if parents are only used in functions where they are required anyway.\n\nThanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6df8a70b56f376560434dd707d7ae5f79acee1db",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-18 17:58:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nthis is the semantics we have right now, where open takes care of the right striping. notice also that even in open we don't always have parent in the request - see mdt_open_by_fid_lock():\n\n        if (ma->ma_valid & MA_PFID) {\n                parent = mdt_object_find(env, mdt, &ma->ma_pfid);",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
